18}}</ref>\n| season2           = 2017\u201318\n| rank2             = 84\n| viewers2          = 5.58\n| 18_49_rating2     = 1.6<ref name=\"entertainment2018\">{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/05/2017-2018-tv-series-ratings-rankings-full-list-of-shows-1202395851/|title=2017-18 TV Series Ratings Rankings: NFL Football, \u2018Big Bang\u2019 Top Charts|website=Deadline Hollywood|date=May 22, 2018|accessdate=May 22, 2018}}</ref>\n\n| link3             = List of American Housewife episodes#Season 3 (2018\u201319)\n| timeslot3         = Wednesday 8:30{{nbsp}}pm {{Small|(1\u201310)}}<br>Tuesday 8:00{{nbsp}}pm {{Small|(11\u201323)}}\n| episodes3         = 23\n| start3            = {{Start date|2018|9|26}}\n| startrating3      = 4.43<ref name=\"3.01\">{{cite web|url=https://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/daily-ratings/wednesday-final-ratings-sept-26-2018/|title=\u2018Chicago Fire\u2019 and \u2018Survivor\u2019 adjusts up, \u2018Star\u2019 adjusts down: Wednesday final ratings|work=TV by the Numbers|last=Welch|first=Alex|date=September 27, 2018|accessdate=September 27, 2018}}</ref>\n| end3              = {{End date|2019|5|21}}\n| endrating3        = 3.64<ref name=\"3.23\">{{cite web|url=https://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/daily-ratings/tuesday-final-ratings-may-21-2019/|title='Mental Samurai,' '1969' adjust down: Tuesday final ratings|last=Welch|first=Alex|work=TV by the Numbers|date=May 22, 2019|accessdate=May 22, 2019}}</ref>\n| season3           = 2018\u201319\n| rank3             = 87\n| viewers3          = 5.46\n| 18_49_rating3     = 1.4\n\n| link4             = List of American Housewife episodes#Season 4 (2019\u201320)\n| timeslot4         = Friday 8:00{{nbsp}}pm {{Small|(1\u201313)}}<br>Wednesday 9:30{{nbsp}}pm {{Small|(14\u201316)}}<ref name=\"New Days & Times 2020\"/><br>Wednesday 9:00{{nbsp}}pm {{Small|(17\u201321)}}<ref name=\"New Days & Times 2020\">{{cite web|title=\"Shark Tank\" Returns to Friday Nights Beginning Friday, Feb. 28, and \"American Housewife\" Moves to Wednesdays at 9 P.M. on April 15|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/news/2020/01/08/shark-tank-returns-to-friday-nights-beginning-friday-feb-28-and-american-housewife-moves-to-wednesdays-at-9-pm-on-april-15-899200/20200108abc07/|work=[[The Futon Critic]]|date=January 8, 2020}}</ref>\n| episodes4         = 21\n| start4            = {{Start date|2019|9|27}}\n| startrating4      = 3.34<ref name=\"4.01\">{{cite web|url=https://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/daily-ratings/friday-final-ratings-sept-27-2019/|title='20/20' adjusts up, 'Masters of Illusion,' 'The Big Stage,' and 'Peaking' adjust down: Friday final ratings|last=Welch|first=Alex|work=TV by the Numbers|date=September 30, 2019|accessdate=September 30, 2019}}</ref>\n| end4              = \n| enrating4        =\n| season4           = 2019\u201320\n| rank4             = \n| viewers4          = \n| 18_49_rating4     =\n\n}}\n\n===Accolades===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"width:99%;\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Award\n! Category\n! Recipient(s)\n! Result\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\"| {{Abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\" | 2017\n| rowspan=\"1\" | [[43rd People's Choice Awards|People's Choice Awards]]\n| Favorite New TV Comedy\n| ''American Housewife''\n| {{nom}}\n| rowspan=\"1\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2016/11/peoples-choice-awards-nominees-2016-full-list-captain-america-kevin-hart-1201854910/ |title=People's Choice Awards Nominees 2017 \u2014 Full List |date=November 15, 2016 |last=Hipes |first=Patrick |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |accessdate=August 24, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6qmSjc8en?url=http://deadline.com/2016/11/peoples-choice-awards-nominees-2016-full-list-captain-america-kevin-hart-1201854910/ |archivedate=May 27, 2017 }}</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\n==Norwalk controversy==\nIn November 2017, the episode \"Boo-Who?\" featured character Taylor Otto dressed up as a \"pregnant Norwalk prom girl\", poking fun at the city of [[Norwalk, Connecticut]], which borders the show's location of [[Westport, Connecticut|Westport]]. Before this incident, there were various other episodes in which Norwalk was mocked: The characters refused to swim in a Norwalk swimming pool, acting like the pool water was diseased because of Norwalk people; one of the children took bets on how many of the girlfriends of Norwalk\u2019s basketball team would be pregnant post season; and Oliver Otto used a neighbor's Hispanic housekeeper to alter flawed Polo shirts and sell them to Norwalk students, believing that no Westport resident would buy them; Oliver ended up earning a lot of money. This brought condemnation from residents, school officials, and politicians of Norwalk. After a petition calling for the producers to stop \"bullying\" Norwalk garnered over 500 signatures and received media coverage, a Disney spokesperson released a statement saying \"As a comedy, ''American Housewife'' isn\u2019t intended to offend anyone. We\u2019ve heard the concerns of the people of Norwalk and have made the decision to omit any mentions of the city from future episodes\".<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thehour.com/news/article/American-Housewife-to-omit-Norwalk-from-future-12390310.php|title=Following outcry, \"American Housewife\" to omit Norwalk from future episodes|author=Kaitlyn Krasselt|date=29 November 2017|accessdate=30 November 2017|newspaper=[[The Hour (newspaper)|The Hour]]}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n<!-- Per [[WP:ELMINOFFICIAL]], choose one official website only -->\n* {{Official website|http://abc.go.com/shows/american-housewife}}\n* {{IMDb title|5396394}}\n\n{{ABCNetwork Shows (current and upcoming)}}\n\n[[Category:2010s American single-camera sitcoms]]\n[[Category:2020s American single-camera sitcoms]]\n[[Category:2010s American LGBT-related comedy television series]]\n[[Category:2020s American LGBT-related comedy television series]]\n[[Category:2016 American television series debuts]]\n[[Category:American Broadcasting Company original programming]]\n[[Category:English-language television programs]]\n[[Category:American LGBT-related sitcoms]]\n[[Category:Television production suspended due to the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]]\n[[Category:Television series about families]]\n[[Category:Television series by ABC Studios]]\n[[Category:Television shows set in Connecticut]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American comedy television series}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name          = American Housewife\n| image              = File:American_Housewife_Logo.svg\n| caption            = \n| genre              = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Sitcom]]\n* Family comedy\n}}\n| creator            = [[Sarah Dunn (author)|Sarah Dunn]]\n| starring           = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Katy Mixon]]\n* [[Diedrich Bader]]\n* [[Meg Donnelly]]\n* [[Daniel DiMaggio]]\n* [[Julia Butters]]\n* [[Ali Wong]]\n* Carly Hughes\n}}\n| narrated           = Katy Mixon \n| composer           = {{Plainlist|\n* Erica Weis\n* Orr Rebhun\n* Jonathan Sadoff {{small|(pilot)}}\n}}\n| country            = United States\n| language           = English\n| num_seasons        = 4\n| num_episodes       = 87\n| list_episodes      = List of American Housewife episodes\n| executive_producer = {{Plainlist|\n* Sarah Dunn\n* Aaron Kaplan \n* Kenny Schwartz \n* Rick Wiener\n* [[Ruben Fleischer]] (pilot only)\n}}\n| producer           = \n| editor             = David L. Bertman\n| location           = \n| cinematography     =\n| camera             = [[Single-camera setup|Single-camera]]\n| runtime            = 22 minutes\n| company            = {{Plainlist|\n* Eight Sisters Productions\n* Weiner & Schwartz Productions\n* [[Kapital Entertainment]]\n* [[ABC Studios]]\n}}\n| distributor        = [[Disney\u2013ABC Domestic Television]]\n| network            = [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]]\n| picture_format     = [[High-definition television|HDTV]] [[720p]]\n| audio_format       = [[5.1 surround sound]]\n| first_aired        = {{Start date|2016|10|11}}\n| last_aired         = {{End date|present}}\n| website            = http://abc.go.com/shows/american-housewife\n| production_website = \n}}\n\n'''''American Housewife''''' is an American [[sitcom]] television series that debuted on October 11, 2016, on [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]]. It is created and written by Sarah Dunn and co-executive produced with Aaron Kaplan, Kenny Schwartz, Rick Wiener, and for the pilot only [[Ruben Fleischer]]. It is a Kapital Entertainment\u2013[[ABC Studios]] co-production.<ref>{{cite web|last=Andreeva |first=Nellie |url=https://deadline.com/2016/05/abc-picks-up-downward-dog-sarah-dunn-comedies-to-series-1201754815/ |title=ABC Picks Up 'Downward Dog' & Sarah Dunn Comedies To Series |website=Deadline Hollywood |date=May 12, 2016 |accessdate=September 29, 2016}}</ref><ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A9JRoZsnINw Preview for \"American Housewife\"] from [[YouTube]]</ref>\n\nIn May 2019, the series was renewed for a fourth season,<ref name=\"S4Renewal\"/> and premiered on September 27, 2019.<ref name=\"SeriesDebutDate\">{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/07/abc-fall-premiere-dates-2019-1202641119/|title=ABC Fall Premiere Dates: 'The Conners', 'Black-ish' & Spinoff, Cobie Smulders' 'Stumptown', Final 'Modern Family' Season & More|work=Deadline Hollywood|first=Erik|last=Pedersen|date=July 2, 2019|accessdate=July 2, 2019}}</ref>\n\n{{TOC limit|3}}\n\n==Premise==\n[[File:LongshoreSailingSchool.JPG|thumb|left|180px|[[Westport, Connecticut]]]]\nThe series chronicles the daily life of Katie Otto, a wife and mother who tries to maintain her sense of self and family while dealing with the wealthy, pretentious, arrogant housewives and their privileged children after moving to the town of [[Westport, Connecticut]]. Compared to the other residents who own big houses, Katie and her family are renters of a more modest home. She lives with Greg, her level-headed husband who is a university professor of history, and their three children. Taylor is their athletic, headstrong, but somewhat dimwitted oldest daughter who wants to fit in with her peers; Oliver, their savvy, ambitious, and snarky son, is the middle child; and Anna-Kat, sweet but obsessive-compulsive, is the youngest and Katie's blatant favorite. Katie frequently vents her frustration to and seeks advice from her two closest friends: Doris, whose strict parenting style sharply contrasts with Katie's; and Angela, a divorced lesbian mother and lawyer with a calm parenting style.\n\n==Episodes==\n{{main|List of American Housewife episodes}}\n{{:List of American Housewife episodes}}\n\n==Cast and characters==\n\n===Main===\n* [[Katy Mixon]] as Kate \"Katie\" Otto\n* [[Diedrich Bader]] as Greg Otto, Katie's husband\n* [[Meg Donnelly]] as Taylor \u201cSweetheart\u201d Otto, Katie and Greg's teenage daughter; <small>the role was portrayed by [[Johnny Sequoyah]] in the televised pilot<!-- SHE WAS CREDITED AS MAIN CAST IN THE PILOT --></small><ref name=\"DonnellyRecasting\">{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2016/07/american-housewife-meg-donnelly-cast-abc-comedy-recasting-1201793752/ |title='American Housewife': Meg Donnelly Added To New ABC Comedy In Recasting |last=Petski |first=Denise |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |date=July 27, 2016 |accessdate=September 9, 2017}}</ref>\n* [[Daniel DiMaggio]] as Oliver Otto, Katie and Greg's teenage son and middle child\n* [[Julia Butters]] as Anna-Kat Otto, Katie and Greg's youngest daughter\n* [[Ali Wong]] as Doris, one of Katie's best friends\n* Carly Hughes as Angela, one of Katie's best friends\n\n===Recurring===\n* [[Leslie Bibb]] as Viv, Katy's neighbor who was originally introduced as Two-Fitbit Lady\n* [[Jessica St. Clair]] as Chloe Brown Mueller, Katie's arch nemesis\n* [[Wendie Malick]] as Kathryn, Katie's mother\n* Logan Pepper as Cooper Bradford, Oliver's uber-wealthy best friend whose parents are almost always out of town; Cooper adores Katie as a mother figure, even when she's strict with the Otto children\n* Amarr M. Wooten as Eyo, Taylor's former boyfriend\n* [[Peyton Meyer]] as Trip Windsor, Taylor's boyfriend\n* Evan O'Toole as Franklin, Anna-Kat's best friend\n* [[Carly Craig]] as Tara Summers\n* [[Sara Rue]] as Nancy Granville\n* Jeannette Sousa as Suzanne\n* [[Jerry Lambert (actor)|Jerry Lambert]] as Principal Ablin\n* [[George Hamilton (actor)|George Hamilton]] as Spencer Blitz, neighbor and one-time billionaire investor who has just returned home, having been out on house arrest after spending 20 years in Federal prison\n* [[Nikki Hahn]] as Gina, Oliver's former girlfriend and fellow ballet dancer\n* Bruno Amato as Louie Tuscadero, Gina's uncle and owner of Tuscadero's Pizza\n* [[Ravi Patel (actor)|Ravi Patel]] as Grant, Greg's assistant\n* Julie Meyer as Maria, Chloe Brown Mueller's employee\n* [[Milo Manheim]] as Pierce, Taylor's former love interest\n* Reylynn Caster as Brie, Oliver's girlfriend\n* [[Matt Shively]] as Lonnie Spears\n\n===Notable guests===\n* [[Kate Flannery]] as Crossing Guard Sandy\n* [[Jenny O'Hara]] as Mrs. Smith\n* [[Timothy Omundson]] as Stan Lawton, Chloe's ex-husband\n* [[Jay Mohr]] as Alan, Viv's ex-husband\n* [[Will Sasso]] as Billy, Katie's childhood best friend\n* [[Tiffani Thiessen]] as Celeste, Angela's ex-wife\n* [[Barry Bostwick]] as Thomas Otto, Greg's father\n* [[Julia Duffy]] as Amanda Otto, Greg's mother\n* [[Mallory Jansen]] as Nina, Oliver's ballet teacher\n* [[Bebe Wood]] as Ellen\n* [[Nathan Fillion]] as himself\n* [[Victoria Justice]] as Harper\n* [[Patrick Duffy]] as Marty, Katie's father\n* [[Ryan Seacrest]] as himself\n* [[Katy Perry]] as herself\n* [[Luke Bryan]] as himself\n* [[Lionel Richie]] as himself\n* [[Thomas Lennon]] as Simon\n* [[Vanessa Lachey]] as Crissy\n* [[Alessandra Ambrosio]] as herself\n* [[Alex Landi]] as himself\n* [[Kelly Ripa]] as Whitney\n* [[Drew Carey]] as Mr. Green\n* [[Ryan Stiles]] as Bill Doty\n* [[Kathy Kinney]] as Lunch Lady\n* [[Ed Weeks]] as Greg Otto, Greg\u2019s British half-brother\n* [[Ian Gomez]] as Brecken Phillips\n\n== Production ==\n=== Development ===\nOn January 28, 2016, it was announced that ABC had given the production a pilot order as ''The Second Fattest Housewife In Westport''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2016/01/second-fattest-housewife-in-westport-comedy-pilot-abc-1201692569/|title=ABC Orders \u2018The Second Fattest Housewife In Westport\u2019 Comedy Pilot|work=Deadline|accessdate=January 28, 2016}}</ref> The episode was written by [[Sarah Dunn (author)|Sarah Dunn]] who was expected to executive produce alongside Aaron Kaplan, Kenny Schwartz and Rick Wiener. Production companies involved with the pilot include Eight Sisters Productions, Weiner & Schwartz Productions, [[Kapital Entertainment]], and [[ABC Studios]]. On May 12, 2016, ABC officially ordered the pilot to series.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2016/05/abc-picks-up-downward-dog-sarah-dunn-comedies-to-series-1201754815/|title=ABC Picks Up \u2018Downward Dog\u2019 & Sarah Dunn Comedies To Series|work=Deadline Hollywood|accessdate=May 12, 2016}}</ref> A few days later, it was announced that the series, now titled ''American Housewife'', would premiere on October 11, 2016 and aired on Tuesdays at 9:30 P.M.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://variety.com/2016/tv/news/abc-fall-premiere-dates-2016-2017-1201805087/|title=ABC Sets 2016\u201317 Fall Premiere Dates for Shondaland Shows, Kiefer Sutherland\u2019s Drama & More|author=Wagmeister, Elizabeth|magazine=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=June 28, 2016|accessdate=June 28, 2016}}</ref> On November 4, 2016, ABC picked up the series for a full season of 22 episodes and on December 13, an additional episode was ordered.<ref name=\"Andreeva\">{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2016/11/american-housewife-full-season-order-abc-real-oneals-1201849120/ |title='American Housewife' Nabs Full-Season Order at ABC, 'The Real O'Neals' Gets 3 More Episodes |last=Andreeva |first=Nellie |website=Deadline Hollywood |date=November 4, 2016 |accessdate=November 5, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"Housewife Speechless\">{{cite web |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/abc-comedies-score-additional-episode-orders-955857/ |title=6 ABC Comedies Score Additional Episode Orders |last=Goldberg |first=Lesley |work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=December 13, 2016|accessdate=December 13, 2016}}</ref> On May 11, 2017, ABC renewed the series for a second season,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2017/05/american-housewife-designaated-survivor-renewed-season-abc-1202090530/|title=\u2018American Housewife\u2019 & \u2018Designated Survivor\u2019 Renewed For Season 2 By ABC|work=Deadline Hollywood|accessdate=May 11, 2017}}</ref> which premiered on September 27, 2017. On May 11, 2018, ABC renewed the series for a third season of 23 episodes,<ref name=\"S3Renewal\">{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/05/american-housewife-renewed-season-3-abc-1202383601/|title=\u2018American Housewife\u2019 Renewed For Season 3 By ABC|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|website=Deadline Hollywood|date=May 11, 2018|accessdate=May 11, 2018}}</ref> which premiered on September 26, 2018. On May 10, 2019, ABC renewed the series for a fourth season<ref name=\"S4Renewal\">{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/05/american-housewife-renewed-season-4-abc-1202605746/|title='American Housewife' Renewed For Season 4 By ABC|website=Deadline Hollywood|first=Erik|last=Pedersen|date=May 10, 2019|accessdate=May 10, 2019}}</ref>; the first 15 episodes began to premiere on September 27, 2019, and <ref name=\"SeriesDebutDate\"/> on November 7, 2019, a back order of six episodes was announced.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/11/american-housewife-bless-this-mess-additional-episodes-abc-back-orders-1202780555/|title=\u2018American Housewife\u2019 & \u2018Bless This Mess\u2019 Get Additional Episodes At ABC|website=Deadline Hollywood|first=Nellie|last=Andreeva|date=November 7, 2019|accessdate=November 7, 2019}}</ref> On March 14, 2020, production on the fourth season was shut down following the [[Impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on television|impact of corona-virus]] outbreak.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2020/03/empire-pose-queen-of-the-south-the-resident-american-housewife-shut-down-coronavirus-1202883591/|title='Empire', 'Pose', 'Queen Of the South', 'The Resident' & 'American Housewife' Shut Down Over Coronavirus|website=Deadline Hollywood|first=Nellie|last=Andreeva|date=March 14, 2020|accessdate=March 14, 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== Casting ===\nOn February 17, 2016, it was announced that [[Katy Mixon]] had been cast in the pilot's lead role.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2016/02/katie-mixon-star-the-second-fattest-housewife-in-westport-abc-pilot-1201704661/|title=Katy Mixon To Play The Lead In \u2018Second Fattest Housewife In Westport\u2019 ABC Pilot|work=Deadline|accessdate=February 17, 2016}}</ref> In March 2016, it was reported that Carly Hughes, [[Ali Wong]] and [[Diedrich Bader]] had also joined the pilot's main cast.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2016/03/apb-fox-drama-pilot-cast-taylor-handley-ward-horton-cbs-bunker-hill-1201711836/|title=\u2018A.P.B.\u2019: Fox Drama Pilot Casts Taylor Handley; Carly Hughes In ABC\u2019s \u2018Second Fattest Housewife\u2019|work=Deadline|accessdate=March 1, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2016/03/four-stars-cbs-pilot-cast-ashley-zukerman-ali-wong-in-abc-second-fattest-housewife-1201713123/|title=\u2018Four Stars\u2019 CBS Pilot Casts Ashley Zukerman; Ali Wong In ABC\u2019s \u2018Second Fattest Housewife\u2019|work=Deadline|accessdate=March 2, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2016/03/diedrich-bader-cast-male-lead-katy-mixon-second-fattest-housewife-in-westport-abc-pilot-1201714535/|title=Diedrich Bader To Co-Star In \u2018The Second Fattest Housewife In Westport\u2019 ABC Pilot|work=Deadline|accessdate=March 4, 2016}}</ref> On June 27, 2016, it was announced that [[Meg Donnelly]] had been cast to replace [[Johnny Sequoyah]] in the pilot role of Taylor, Katie and Greg's character's daughter.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2016/07/american-housewife-meg-donnelly-cast-abc-comedy-recasting-1201793752/|title=\u2018American Housewife\u2019: Meg Donnelly Added To New ABC Comedy In Recasting|work=Deadline|accessdate=June 27, 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n\n===Critical response===\n''American Housewife'' has received mixed reviews from television critics, with Katy Mixon's performance being praised as the show's highlight. [[Review aggregator]] website [[Rotten Tomatoes]] reported an approval rating of 54%, based on 28 reviews, with an average rating of 6.1/10. The site's critical consensus reads, \"''American Housewife'' is boosted by a strong and enjoyable lead performance by Katy Mixon, yet her performance alone strains to sustain an excessively quirky show that relies too heavily on stereotypes.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/american_housewife/s01/#contentReviews|title=American Housewife: Season 1 (2016)|work=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|accessdate=October 31, 2016}}</ref> [[Metacritic]] reported a score of 60 out of 100, based on 25 critics, indicating \"mixed or average reviews\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.metacritic.com/tv/american-housewife|title=American Housewife: Season 1|website=[[Metacritic]]|accessdate=October 31, 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Ratings===\n{{Television season ratings\n| link1             = List of American Housewife episodes#Season 1 (2016\u201317)\n| timeslot1         = Tuesday 8:30{{nbsp}}pm\n| episodes1         = 23\n| start1            = {{Start date|2016|10|11}}\n| startrating1      = 6.61<ref name=\"1.01\">{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/daily-ratings/tuesday-final-ratings-oct-11-2016/|title='The Voice,' 'NCIS,' 'Flash' and ABC comedies adjust up, 'No Tomorrow' adju